### Modal Centering Pattern (Critical)
**Problem**: Modals not centered in viewport, sidebar not blurred, modal offset to left
**Root Cause**: Modal element positioned inside a container (e.g., `#requestarr-section`) that's scoped to content area only
**Solution**: Modal MUST be direct child of body/root container to cover full viewport

#### Correct Modal Structure:
```html
<!-- WRONG - Modal inside section container -->
<div id="some-section" class="content-section">
    <!-- ... section content ... -->
    <div id="modal" class="modal">...</div>  <!-- ‚ùå Can't cover sidebar -->
</div>

<!-- CORRECT - Modal outside section container -->
<div id="some-section" class="content-section">
    <!-- ... section content ... -->
</div>
<!-- Modal at same level as section -->
<div id="modal" class="modal">...</div>  <!-- ‚úÖ Covers full viewport -->
```

#### Correct Modal CSS:
```css
/* Modal overlay - covers entire viewport with blur */
.modal {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.85);
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
    display: none; /* or flex when shown */
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    z-index: 9999;
    padding: 20px;
}

