```

#### Key Requirements:
- Modal element must be outside any content-scoped containers
- Use `position: fixed` with `top/left/right/bottom: 0` for full viewport coverage
- Single element approach: modal itself is the backdrop (no separate backdrop div needed)
- Use flexbox (`display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center`) for true centering
- `backdrop-filter: blur(8px)` on the modal overlay blurs entire page including sidebar
- High z-index (9999+) ensures modal appears above all other content

#### Anti-Patterns to Avoid:
- ‚ùå Nesting modal inside section/content containers
- ‚ùå Using `margin-left` offsets to compensate for sidebar (breaks centering)
- ‚ùå Separate backdrop div that interferes with positioning
- ‚ùå Relative positioning or limited width/height containers
- ‚ùå Low z-index values that allow content to show through

